-- Lufthansa Plans 1.5 Billion-Euro Savings Program, DPA Reports
-- B y   A l e x   W e b b
-- 2012-01-31T08:05:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-31/lufthansa-plans-1-5-billion-euro-savings-program-dpa-reports.html
Deutsche Lufthansa AG (LHA)  plans to save
1.5 billion euros annually through a savings program to
centralize some of its business units’ operations, Deutsche
Presse Agentur reported, citing Karl Ulrich Garnadt, the head of
Lufthansa’s cargo business.  Purchasing will be one of the competencies administered
centrally, DPA reported Garnadt as saying, confirming earlier
press reports.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Webb  in Frankfurt 
 awebb25@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chad Thomas at   cthomas16@bloomberg.net . 